# Spotify “now playing” (optional — widget hides if unset)
# 1. Create an app at https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
# 2. Redirect URIs in Spotify Dashboard (must match what we send):
#    Local: http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/spotify/callback  (Spotify disallows "localhost")
#    Prod:  https://YOUR_DOMAIN/api/spotify/callback
#    The app maps localhost → 127.0.0.1 automatically for the OAuth redirect_uri.
# 3. Copy Client ID and Client Secret below
# 4. Get refresh token: open /api/spotify/auth on the SAME origin you’ll use (local or deployed),
#    sign in to Spotify, copy SPOTIFY_REFRESH_TOKEN from the callback page into .env.local.
#    If we add new Spotify scopes (e.g. recently played), visit /api/spotify/auth again to re-approve.
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=
SPOTIFY_REFRESH_TOKEN=

# Optional: force callback URL (use if your host/proxy gives wrong request URL)
# SPOTIFY_REDIRECT_URI=https://YOUR_DOMAIN/api/spotify/callback

